Privacy Policy
INTRODUCTION
WarthogLab (“we,” “us,” or “our”) respects your privacy and is committed to protecting your personal information. This Privacy Policy (“Policy”) explains how we collect, use, share, and protect information obtained through our mobile applications (“Apps”) available on the Apple App Store and Google Play Store, including but not limited to “Universal Remote Control TV,” “AI Note Taker,” and other apps we may publish.
When we refer to “personal data” or “personal information,” we mean any data relating to an identified or identifiable individual. This Policy applies to all users and others who access or use our Apps (“Users”). As a French company operating in accordance with European data protection regulations, we act as the data controller for the personal information processed via our Apps, unless otherwise stated.
By installing, accessing, or using our Apps, you acknowledge that you have read, understood, and agree to this Privacy Policy.
CONTACT INFORMATION
If you have questions or concerns about your privacy or this Policy, please contact us at:
WarthogLab
Email:
contact@warthoglab.com
Registered and resident in France
INFORMATION WE COLLECT
We may collect different types of information related to your use of our Apps, including:
1.
Information You Provide Voluntarily
:
•
Contact Data
: For example, when you reach out to us via email or other support channels, we may collect your email address and the content of your message.
•
Feedback and Support Requests
: Any data you provide when giving feedback or reporting issues may be retained as necessary to address and resolve your request.
2.
Information Collected Automatically
:
When you use our Apps, certain information may be collected automatically for operational and analytical purposes. This may include:
•
Device Information
: Device model, operating system version, unique device identifiers (such as Advertising IDs), language settings, country, and time zone.
•
Usage Data
: App usage metrics, the screens you view, the features you interact with, crash reports, and diagnostic data.
•
Log Files
: IP addresses, session start and end times, and other technical information needed to provide and improve the Apps.
3.
Third-Party Services and SDKs
:
Our Apps integrate with third-party services, which may collect information on our behalf or provide us with aggregated data. These services include but are not limited to:
•
Analytics and Infrastructure
: Firebase by Google (for analytics, crash reports, and app performance metrics)
•
Advertising and Monetization
: Google Admob (for delivering ads), RevenueCat (for handling in-app purchases and subscriptions)
These third-party services may collect device identifiers, usage data, IP addresses, and other data as described in their respective privacy policies. We do not control these services’ tracking technologies and their subsequent use of data. Please consult their privacy policies for more information:
HOW WE USE YOUR INFORMATION
We use the collected data for the following purposes:
1.
To Operate and Maintain Our Apps
:
We process your data to deliver core functionality, ensure stability, and provide the features you expect.
2.
To Improve Our Services
:
We analyze usage data and feedback to enhance performance, fix bugs, and develop new features or products.
3.
To Personalize User Experience and Advertising
:
We may use analytics and advertising data to serve more relevant ads and content, subject to your consent where required by law.
4.
To Communicate with You
:
If you contact us, we may use your email address and message to respond and provide support.
5.
To Enforce Our Terms and Comply with Legal Obligations
:
We may use your information to prevent fraud, enforce our Terms of Use, or comply with regulatory requirements.
LEGAL BASES FOR PROCESSING
For Users in the European Economic Area (EEA), United Kingdom, or Switzerland, we process your personal data under the following legal bases, as applicable:
• Your consent (e.g., for certain analytics or advertising)
• Our legitimate interests (e.g., improving the Apps, ensuring security, and preventing fraud)
• Performance of a contract (e.g., providing requested App features)
• Compliance with legal obligations
SHARING YOUR INFORMATION
We do not rent or sell your personal data. We may share information with:
•
Service Providers
: Third parties that assist us in providing services, such as analytics, hosting, customer support, or payment processing.
•
Law Enforcement or Legal Requests
: Where required by law or when we believe in good faith that disclosure is necessary to protect our rights, Users’ safety, or investigate fraud.
INTERNATIONAL DATA TRANSFERS
We are based in France and may transfer, store, or process your personal data in other countries, including outside the EEA. If we transfer your data internationally, we ensure an adequate level of data protection through recognized legal mechanisms.
DATA RETENTION
We retain personal data for as long as necessary to fulfill the purposes outlined in this Policy unless a longer retention period is required or permitted by law. When no longer needed, we will securely delete or anonymize your data.
YOUR RIGHTS AND CHOICES
Depending on your jurisdiction, you may have rights regarding your personal data, including:
• The right to access, correct, or delete your personal data.
• The right to object to or restrict processing.
• The right to data portability.
• The right to withdraw consent at any time, where processing is based on consent.
To exercise your rights, please contact us at
contact@warthoglab.com
. We will respond in accordance with applicable law.
OPTING OUT OF INTEREST-BASED ADVERTISING AND ANALYTICS
• For iOS devices, you can limit ad tracking in Settings > Privacy & Security > Tracking.
• For Android devices, you can opt out of personalized ads by adjusting your Advertising settings in Google services.
• You can also uninstall or stop using our Apps at any time if you do not agree to this Policy.
CHILDREN’S PRIVACY
Our Apps are not intended for children under the age of 13. We do not knowingly collect personal data from children. If we become aware of such collection without parental consent, we will take steps to delete the data promptly. If you believe we have collected information about a child, please contact us.
SECURITY
We take reasonable measures to protect your data, but no security measures are perfect. We cannot guarantee absolute security. If we become aware of a data breach involving your personal data, we will notify you in accordance with applicable law.
CHANGES TO THIS PRIVACY POLICY
We may update this Policy from time to time. Any changes will be posted within the Apps or on our website. Your continued use of the Apps after changes are posted constitutes your acceptance of such changes.
HOW TO CONTACT US
If you have any questions about this Privacy Policy or our data practices, please contact us at:
